idental parallelism you *can* get with a single one is really very <br />accidental indeed).<br /><br />Of course, it should be tested in -next for a while regardless. And talk <br />to the networkng people, who are the main user of workqueues.<br /><br />			Linus<br /><br /><br /></pre><div align="center"><div class="shariff" data-services="[&quot;reddit&quot;]" data-theme="grey" data-lang="en" data-backend-url="//shariff.lkml.org/index.php"></div></div></td><td width="32" rowspan="2" class="c" valign="top"><img src="/images/icornerr.gif" width="32" height="32" alt="\" /></td></tr><tr><td align="right" valign="bottom">
